"    <div id=\"topicTitle\">",
"     Patient information: Sepsis in adults (The Basics)",
"    </div>",
"    <span class=\"view\">",
"     View in",
"     <a class=\"lang\" href=\"./es-419/sepsis-in-adults-the-basics?source=topic_page\">",
"      Spanish",
"     </a>",
"    </span>",
"    <a class=\"contributor contributor_credentials\" href=\"./authors-and-editors/patient-information\">",
"     Written by the doctors and editors at UpToDate",
"    </a>",
"    <div id=\"topicText\">",
"     <p class=\"headingAnchor\" id=\"H12436487\">",
"      <span class=\"h1\">",
"       What is sepsis?",
"      </span>",
"      &nbsp;&mdash;&nbsp;Sepsis is a serious illness that happens when an infection affects the whole body in a certain way. Sepsis can happen in anyone, but it is more likely to happen in people who:",
"     </p>",
"     <p>",
"      <ul class=\"bulletCompact-block\">",
"       <li>",
"        Are older or bedridden",
"       </li>",
"       <li>",
"        Are staying in the hospital or have had recent surgery",
"       </li>",
"       <li>",
"        Have thin tubes such as catheters or IVs in their body",
"       </li>",
"       <li>",
"        Have a weak infection-fighting system",
"       </li>",
"      </ul>",
"     </p>",
"     <p>",
"      Sepsis needs to be treated quickly. If it is not treated, it can become severe. Severe sepsis can lead to a life-threatening condition called &ldquo;septic shock.&rdquo;",
"     </p>",
"     <p class=\"headingAnchor\" id=\"H12436502\">",
"      <span class=\"h1\">",
"       What are the symptoms of sepsis?",
"      </span>",
"      &nbsp;&mdash;&nbsp;Symptoms of sepsis can include:",
"     </p>",
"     <p>",
"      <ul class=\"bulletCompact-block\">",
"       <li>",
"        A fever &ndash; But some people get a low body temperature instead of a fever.",
"       </li>",
"       <li>",
"        Chills",
"       </li>",
"       <li>",
"        Breathing that is very fast",
"       </li>",
"       <li>",
"        A heartbeat that is very fast",
"       </li>",
"      </ul>",
"     </p>",
"     <p>",
"      Symptoms of severe sepsis can include:",
"     </p>",
"     <p>",
"      <ul class=\"bullet-block\">",
"       <li>",
"        Acting confused or feeling light-headed",
"       </li>",
"       <li>",
"        Trouble breathing",
"       </li>",
"       <li>",
"        Cool clammy skin or red flushed skin",
"       </li>",
"       <li>",
"        Urinating much less than usual",
"       </li>",
"       <li>",
"        Different types of skin rashes &ndash; One type is a lacy, purple rash that is usually on the legs, but can also be on the arms. Another rash looks like red or purple spots on the skin that do not go away when touched. These spots are usually on the chest and legs, but can also be in other areas.",
"       </li>",
"       <li>",
"        Other problems with the heart, kidneys, or brain",
"       </li>",
"      </ul>",
"     </p>",
"     <p>",
"      People who have septic shock have many of the symptoms listed above, plus their blood pressure gets low.",
"     </p>",
"     <p class=\"headingAnchor\" id=\"H12436517\">",
"      <span class=\"h1\">",
"       Should I see the doctor or nurse?",
"      </span>",
"      &nbsp;&mdash;&nbsp;Yes, as soon as possible. Many people who get sepsis are already in a hospital. But if you are not in a hospital, you (or the person with you) should call the doctor or nurse if you:",
"     </p>",
"     <p>",
"      <ul class=\"bulletCompact-block\">",
"       <li>",
"        Have a fever and chills, and have any of the symptoms above or look very sick",
"       </li>",
"       <li>",
"        Have had a recent surgery or hospital stay, and now are sick or have an infection",
"       </li>",
"      </ul>",
"     </p>",
"     <p>",
"      If your doctor or nurse is unable to see you immediately, or you can&rsquo;t reach him or her, you should go to the nearest emergency room.",
"     </p>",
"     <p class=\"headingAnchor\" id=\"H12436532\">",
"      <span class=\"h1\">",
"       Will I have tests?",
"      </span>",
"      &nbsp;&mdash;&nbsp;Probably. Your doctor will learn about your symptoms and do an exam. He or she will likely do tests to look for an infection, see if the infection has spread to your blood, and see how serious your condition is. These tests can include:",
"     </p>",
"     <p>",
"      <ul class=\"bullet-block\">",
"       <li>",
"        Blood tests, including a test called &ldquo;blood cultures&rdquo;",
"       </li>",
"       <li>",
"        Urine tests",
"       </li>",
"       <li>",
"        Lab tests &ndash; For example, if you are coughing up mucus, your doctor can test your mucus for bacteria.",
"       </li>",
"       <li>",
"        X-rays or imaging tests &ndash; Imaging tests can create pictures of the inside of your body.",
"       </li>",
"      </ul>",
"     </p>",
"     <p class=\"headingAnchor\" id=\"H12436547\">",
"      <span class=\"h1\">",
"       How is sepsis treated?",
"      </span>",
"      &nbsp;&mdash;&nbsp;Sepsis and septic shock are usually treated in the hospital with:",
"     </p>",
"     <p>",
"      <ul class=\"bullet-block\">",
"       <li>",
"        Antibiotics that go in your vein through an IV",
"       </li>",
"       <li>",
"        Fluids that go in your vein through an IV",
"       </li>",
"       <li>",
"        Other medicines to treat your condition &ndash; For example, if your blood pressure is too low, your doctor can give you medicine to raise it.",
"       </li>",
"      </ul>",
"     </p>",
"     <p>",
"      If an IV or catheter in your body is causing your sepsis, your doctor might take the IV or catheter out.",
"     </p>",
"     <p>",
"      Some people are also treated with surgery. If you have a severe infection of the skin or tissue under the skin, your doctor might do surgery to remove the infected areas.",
"     </p>",
"     <p class=\"headingAnchor\" id=\"H12436562\">",
"      <span class=\"h1\">",
"       Can sepsis be prevented?",
"      </span>",
"      &nbsp;&mdash;&nbsp;You can help prevent sepsis by:",
"     </p>",
"     <p>",
"      <ul class=\"bullet-block\">",
"       <li>",
"        Getting treated right away if you get an infection",
"       </li>",
"       <li>",
"        Avoiding infections &ndash; One way to avoid infections is to get the vaccines your doctor recommends. Vaccines are treatments that can prevent serious infections. If you have a child, make sure he or she gets the recommended vaccines, too.",
"       </li>",
"      </ul>",
"     </p>",
"     <p class=\"headingAnchor\" id=\"H12436577\">",
"      <span class=\"h1\">",
"       More on this topic",
"      </span>",
